          "settings": {
            "text": "The meaning behind Toi et Moi promise rings",
            "heading_tag": "h1"
          }
        },
        "richtext_KAtYgB": {
          "type": "richtext",
          "settings": {
            "content": "<p>The beauty of a Toi et Moi promise ring lies in its symbolism. Each stone represents one person, and together they create a design that reflects unity, balance and connection.<br/><br/>Unlike traditional single-stone rings, this style tells a more complete story. It represents:<br/><br/>•⁠  ⁠Two people with their own identities<br/>•⁠  ⁠A shared connection built on trust and loyalty<br/>•⁠  ⁠Balance between individuality and togetherness<br/>•⁠  ⁠A promise that exists equally between both people<br/><br/>This is why Toi et Moi rings have remained meaningful for centuries, with the design dating back to iconic romantic gestures such as Napoleon’s proposal in 1796<br/><br/></p>"
          }
        }
      },
